Bhai ab baat karte hain ek aur **important aur confusing keyword** ki â€”
## ğŸ”’ `final` keyword in Java (Hinglish + Deep)

---

### ğŸ“Œ Definition:
> `final` ka matlab hai:
> **â€œek baar assign ya define kar diya, ab usko change nahi kar sakteâ€**

`final` ek **restriction** lagata hai:
- Variable: value change nahi ho sakti
- Method: override nahi ho sakta
- Class: inherit nahi ho sakti

---

## ğŸ”° Use Cases of `final`:

| `final` kis ke saath use hota hai? | Kya restrict karta hai?                           |
|------------------------------------|--------------------------------------------------|
| `final variable`                   | value ko reassign nahi kar sakte                |
| `final method`                     | subclass us method ko override nahi kar sakta   |
| `final class`                      | class ko extend/inherit nahi kar sakte          |

---

## ğŸ”¹ 1. Final Variable

```java
public class TestFinalVariable {
    final int speedLimit = 60;

    void run() {
        // speedLimit = 100; âŒ Error â€“ can't change final variable
        System.out.println("Speed Limit: " + speedLimit);
    }
}
```

---

## ğŸ”¹ 2. Final Method

```java
class Vehicle {
    final void run() {
        System.out.println("Vehicle is running");
    }
}

class Bike extends Vehicle {
    // void run() {} âŒ Error â€“ can't override final method
}
```

---

## ğŸ”¹ 3. Final Class

```java
final class Calculator {
    int add(int a, int b) {
        return a + b;
    }
}

// class AdvancedCalc extends Calculator {} âŒ Error â€“ can't inherit final class
```

---

## ğŸ’¡ Bonus: Final with Reference Variables

```java
final Student s = new Student("Samad");

// s = new Student("Ayan"); âŒ Not allowed â€“ can't change reference
s.name = "Ayan";           // âœ… Allowed â€“ object state can be changed
```

> ğŸ’¬ `final` ref ka matlab: object ki **reference** change nahi hogi, par uski **properties** change ho sakti hain.

---

## âš ï¸ Interview Tricks:

| Question                                           | Answer                                                  |
|----------------------------------------------------|---------------------------------------------------------|
| Can we reassign final variable?                    | âŒ No                                                    |
| Can a final method be inherited?                   | âœ… Yes, but âŒ can't override                            |
| Can we override a final method?                    | âŒ No                                                    |
| Can a final class be extended?                     | âŒ No                                                    |
| Can final reference variableâ€™s internal state change? | âœ… Yes (object state mutable, reference immutable)     |

---

## ğŸ§  Use Cases in Real World:
- Constants: `final double PI = 3.14;`
- Secure Utility Classes: `final class Math {}`
- Prevent Override: `final void logData()`

